  "text": "Such polynomials were introduced by Cohn in 1922 and were used by [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] to synthesize low order suboptimal controllers. It turns out that results completely analogous to Facts 1 and 2 hold for a SISO system if its associated polynomial is superstable. On the other hand, it is worth noticing that the standard conversion of a SISO system in the form (17), e.g. an nth order difference equation, to the state space form (4) does not yield a superstable matrix. This suggest that the results presented here for MIMO systems can be expanded to larger classes of systems and that in some cases (at least SISO) superstability is a structural property, independent of the coordinate system chosen for the state-space realization.",
